## lte variable

> This API is provided as a preview for developers and may change based on feedback that we receive. Do not use this API in a production environment.
> 

Returns `true` if the first argument is less than or equal to the second; otherwise `false`

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
lte: <T extends string | number | bigint>(a: T, b: T) => boolean
```

## Example 1


```ts
// Number
lte(1, 2) // true
lte(2, 2) // true
lte(2, 1) // false

```

## Example 2


```ts
// Bigint
lte(1n, 2n) // true
lte(2n, 2n) // true
lte(2n, 1n) // true

```

## Example 3


```ts
// String
lte('a', 'z') // true
lte('a', 'a') // true
lte('z', 'a') // false

```
